      • addStaticPrefix

        default CommandPluginBuilder addStaticPrefix(java.lang.String prefix)
        This adds a module that implements PrefixPlugin to provide a static prefix that cannot be changed. If a PrefixPlugin is not added, one will be provided with a static prefix of "!"

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultPrefixModule(prefix))

        You can define a different prefix implementation by providing an object to addModule(ICommandModule) that implements IPrefixModule

        Parameters:
        prefix - a string the defines a global prefix
        Returns:
        this

      • addAdminPlugin

        default CommandPluginBuilder addAdminPlugin()
        This enables the @Admin annotation that is marked on Command classes. This ensures that Commands marked with @Admin are only usable by Administrators.

        It is important to include an implementation of AdminModule through either this method, BreadBotBuilder.addAdminPlugin(Predicate), or your own implementation. Otherwise, all users will have access to Administrative Commands

        The default criteria for defining an Administrator is as follows:

        • Has Kick Members Permission
        • Is higher than the bot on the role hierarchy

        Different criteria to determine which member has administrative status with BreadBotBuilder.addAdminPlugin(Predicate) or your own implementation of AdminPlugin

        Returns:
        this

      • addAdminPlugin

        default CommandPluginBuilder addAdminPlugin(java.util.function.Predicate<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Member> isAdmin)
        Define custom behavior to determine which members can use Commands marked with @Admin

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultAdminModule(isAdmin))
        Parameters:
        isAdmin - a Predicate that can determine which members are Admins
        Returns:
        this

      • addOwnerPlugin

        default CommandPluginBuilder addOwnerPlugin(long... owners)
        Allows the @Owner annotation to be used. If one or more ids are provided as an argument to this method, then only those id's are recognized as being able to use a command marked with @Owner. If no ids are provided to this method, the only owner recognized is the application owner.
        Parameters:
        owners - the ids of the owners
        Returns:
        this
